%% Diagram: Two Generals reduction — exactly-once delivery cannot be solved by finite acks
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant A as General A (sender)
    participant N as Unreliable channel
    participant B as General B (receiver)

    A->>N: "Attack at dawn"
    N->>B: deliver (or drop)
    Note right of B: Did A's message arrive? If dropped, B never attacks.

    B->>N: ack #1
    N->>A: deliver (or drop)
    Note left of A: Did B receive the order? If ack dropped, A cannot be sure.

    A->>N: ack of ack
    N->>B: deliver (or drop)
    Note right of B: Did A receive my ack? Uncertainty regresses forever.

    Note over A,B: Each side needs the other's last message confirmed - impossible over a lossy channel in finite rounds. Reduction: an "exactly-once delivery" protocol would solve Two Generals.
